#
#  CATLOW library - collection of potentials based
#  around the Catlow oxygen-oxygen potential
#
#  O2    general O2- species
#  O1    oxygen in hydroxyl group, OH-
#  H1    hydrogn in hydroxyl group, OH-
#
#  References:
#  (0) M.J.Sanders, M.J.Leslie and C.R.A.Catlow J.Chem.Soc.Chem.Com 1271 1984
#  (1) R.A.Jackson and C.R.A.Catlow Mole. Sim. 1 207-224 1988.
#  (2) K.P.Schroder, J.Sauer, M.Leslie, C.R.A.Catlow and
#      J.M.Thomas, Chem. Phys. Lett., 188 (1992) 320.
#  (3) J.D.Gale and N.J.Henson, JCS Faraday Trans., 90
#      (1994) 3175.
#  (4) J.D.Gale, unpublished results - non-zeolite potentials
#      are relax fitted to structure and any available properties
#      for the relevant binary oxide
#  (5) A.Jentys and C.R.A.Catlow Catalysis Lett. 22 251-257 1993.
#      for Ti(IV)-O(II)
#  (6) D.W.Lewis,C.R.A.Catlow,G.Sankar and S.W.Carr 1995
#      J.Phys.Chem 99 2377-2383 1995  for Fe(III)-O(II) and OH
#  (7) C.J.J.den Ouden,R.A.Jackson,C.R.A.Catlow and M.F.M.Post
#      J.Phys.Chem. 94 5286-5290 1990   for Ni(II)-O(II)
#
#  NB no potential parameters have been derived for X-O_OH
#     and X-H_OH where X=K,Sr,Ti etc.
#
species
Mg    core  2.00000
Ni    core  2.00000.
O2    core  0.86902
O2    shel -2.86902

buckingham
Mg core    O2    shel   946.627 0.31813  0.00000 0.0 10.0
Ni core    O2    shel  1582.500 0.28820  0.00000 0.0 10.0
O2 shel    O2    shel 22764.000 0.14900 27.87900 0.0 12.0
O2 shel    O1    core 22764.000 0.14900 27.87900 0.0 12.0


spring
O2  74.92

